Many years after their demise, veteran actor, Kanayo O. Kanayo has remembered his loving parents. The thespian shared their photo seated side-by-side as he recollected his father’s motto. According to KOK, his father always emphasised the need for people to live in contentment. He also asked his fans and followers to share their father’s watchword. Kanayo wrote: “June 24 . In loving memory of my parents, Mr & Mrs Donatus & Isabella Onyekwere. “My father always said, BE CONTENT WITH WHATEVER YOU HAVE. What did your father always say?” Responding to the actor’s post, many had several mantras of their fathers to share. Dichukwu said: “Somebody’s progress, wealth, riches should not give u sleepless night at all. Just work hard, pray hard & be upright…”   Reactions over DaBaby, Davido collabo     Uche Maduagwu to Tonto Dikeh: Jesus anointed your womb to…     Never share girlfriends’ secrets with your partners – Elsie…   amaka_depos wrote: “Ukpana okpoko gburu nti chiri ya”. The grasshopper that is killed by okpoko (a bird dat usually makes noice when arriving) is deaf (Once forewarned of danger, flee except you are deaf). dridri.flore stated: “Do good and keep walking. God will surely send you a helper in your own time of needs.” evaristusidogbe said: “My father always says “there is a challenge out there, but the big challenge would first start from HOME”….. it’s manifesting already.” kellz_boi wrote: “My dad would always tell us to pray and work hard… Never to envy anyone else even if they seem to be doing better than us… He’d always say everything here on earth has its own time…” ikennaohiri stated: “Always have your head on your shoulders.” bahdestchriskhalifa said: “There is God and there is light. Work and Grace will speak for you.” nadmedics wrote: “Business before pleasure.” vicky_qute stated: “Conserve what you have to get what you want.”